\title{Symmetric and Antisymmetric Matrix}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-05-26}
\taxon{definition}
\import{ela}

\p{Let #{\mat{A}} be an #{n\times n} matrix. We call #{\mat{A}} \define{Symmetric} if it is equal to its transpose: #{\mat{A}=\transpose{\mat{A}}}.}

\p{Similarly, we call #{\mat{A}} \define{Antisymmetric} if it is the negation of its transpose #{\mat{A}=-\transpose{\mat{A}}}.}

